==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*lakhsa-'', from Indo-European ''*lakso-''.  Cognate with Old High German [[lahs]] (German [[Lachs]]), Old Norse [[lax]] (Swedish [[lax]]).  The IE root is also the source of Lithuanian [[lašiša]], Latvian [[lasis]], Russian [[лосось]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /læaks/

===Noun===
'''leax''' ''m''
# a [[salmon]]

